The country is fine from Findlay St unclear Wayne not so good from unclear Logansport but very good from Logansport unclear near Lafayette from there to attica it is rathert broken but a beautiful country. The country is good nearly all through Ill but grows better as you approach Decatur where it is very fine.

Oct. 11 Went to the Fair. Made a tour of the grounds which are very fine. Went through the Art Building where one could spend a week and not see the half. was most interested in the French Jappanese and Russian exhibits but all are so good that it would take a critic to distinguish between them.
Machinery Hall was next visited which is to big to be taken in in one day.
Transportation Builg is very interesting and instructive.

On the Pike. The Bowery Deep Sea Diving and Creation was visited. /The first two are fakes but Creation is noe of the finest things I ever saw. We left the grounds at seven PM very tired and willing to go to bed.
Oct 12.
West to the City for a change. Went through the Union Station which is one of the finest in the United States. Went over the Missippi River to East St Louis and took a car from there to Belleville Ill a very

pretty town in a nice country. Came back to St. L. and went over the finest part of the city. Came to the hotel at seven wrote a letter and went to bed.
Oct 13
Went to the Fair at 9 A.M. Made a pretty thorough tour through the agricultural Building and Electric Building and spent two or three hours in the Varied Industry Building which is very fine and would take a week to go through it properly. Was more

interested in Japan's section than any other exhibit Spent part of the evening around the Lagoon. The Cascades Electric display and buildings wery very beautiful. 
On the Pike was in to see the Girl from Madrid which was good. Moorish Palace, a fake and A Trip to Paris. F first class entertainment. Left the grounds for my hotel at 9 o'clock.

Oct 14
Visited the Phillip-ene villages. Saw the native soldiers parade which was equal to any white soldiers.
Went net to Horticusal Hall, which was very good but the hall was not nearly full.
Visited the stock pens and then went to the Boer War. These was an immense crowd and the show first class.
Then went through Manufacurers Building. The exhibits in this building were all good among the very best

was the Simmons Hardware display.
Went down the Pike going into the Tyrolean Alps. A Beer Garden. The scenery was grand.
Peggy from Paris. Radium dances and songs were very fine. Left the grounds at 8:30.
Oct 15
Went to the Forest Fish and Game exhibit through the Educational Building Place of Liberal Arts US Government Building Mining and Metallurgy and two or three of the smaller buildings. 
All are good.

Oct 15
Went to the city. Took forty five mile boat ride down the river. Got back to the city at one o'clock. After dinner went over the city for an hour and then took a suburban car to St. Charles about twenty miles north west of St. Louis just across the Missouri river. It is a fine trip through a beautiful country. Well worth the time and money it costs. Got back to hotel at 7. Tired but well pleased with the days work.

Oct 16
Went to City in morning and then to Fair. Went through Missouri and Louisiana State Buildings. Saw the U.S. Navy exhibit and then made a second tour through Liberal Arts Manufacturers and Varied Industries buildings. The balance of the day ws spent in purchasing souvenirs, attending Band Concerts etc.

Oct. 17
Took a mile around the grounds on the International RR. Then went through the Ohio, New York, Mass. and Missippi State buildings which are only interesting as homes or resting places for visitors except Miss where Jefferson Davis' last home is reproduced the bed upon which he died. The clothes he wore when captured his furniture pictured etc. Went through the buildings of France

Cuba, Brazil Belgium Italy and Australia. All are good but the art collection in France's building I think is the best there is at the fair. I then went to see the Jubilee Presents given to Queen Victoria Remained for the fine works in the evening which were the best I ever saw.

Oct 19 1904
Made my farewell visit to the Fair. Went through the Washington State Building which is very interesting. through the Anthropology building where the antiquities of Egypt and many other countries are on exhibition. went then to the Smithsonian Institute exhibit and then to a few other places of minor importance before leaving for the city to take the train for home We left St Louis at 9.02 PM
and arrived in Findlay at 10 the following morning thus ending a most agreeable and
